</picture></div><p>If you're passionate about properties and the work that goes into successfully managing them, you might be wondering how to turn your interests into a profitable business. We've formulated this guide to show you how to do precisely that.</p></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-property-management-business-section1" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>1.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=choose-a-business-name>Choose a business name.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-property-management-business-section1-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=jot-down-your-ideas>Jot down your ideas.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-jot-down-your-ideas-288x288-20200819.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Jot down your ideas."></div></div><p>Your property management company needs a name that is easily recognizable and memorable. As you begin creating your business, you need to decide on a name that will help you to stand out. Start by writing down your ideas.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Use <a
href="https://www.namesnack.com/">NameSnack</a> to find property management business name ideas if you need a hand.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-property-management-business-section1-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=pick-a-name-that-inspires-confidence-in-people>Pick a name that inspires confidence in people.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-pick-a-name-that-inspires-confidence-in-people-288x288-20200819.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Pick a name that inspires confidence in people."></div></div><p>Top property management companies like Pinnacle, Alliance Real Estate, and Lincoln Property Company have names that sound organized and professional. You want to choose a name that communicates a sense of trust.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Your target market will be able to help you do this. Consider posting questionnaires on your social media platforms and in property management groups to obtain feedback.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-property-management-business-section1-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=trademark-your-business-name>Trademark your business name.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-apply-for-a-trademark-288x288-20200819.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Trademark your business name."></div></div><p>If you have decided on a property management business name, make sure that you <a
href="https://www.namesnack.com/guides/how-to-trademark-a-name">secure a trademark</a> as soon as possible so that no one else takes it. You can register a trademark at
<a
href="https://www.uspto.gov/trademarks/apply">www.uspto.gov</a>.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-property-management-business-section2" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>2.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=create-a-business-plan>Create a business plan.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-property-management-business-section2-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=familiarize-yourself-with-the-key-elements-of-a-business-plan>Familiarize yourself with the key elements of a business plan.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-familiarize-yourself-with-the-key-elements-of-a-business-plan-288x288-20200819.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Familiarize yourself with the key elements of a business plan."></div></div><p>A business plan should outline the purpose of your business and any practical steps that you intend to take to establish and grow the business. Writing a plan for your property management business will help you to organize your strategy and present your vision to potential investors or stakeholders.</p><p>Your property management business plan should include the following:</p><ul><li>Executive summary.</li><li>Company description.</li><li>Products and services.</li><li>Marketing plan.</li><li>Operational plan.</li><li>Management.</li><li>Financial plan/projections.</li></ul><p>Your business plan can be a point of reference as you launch your property management company.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-property-management-business-section2-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>2.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=formulate-your-business-plan>Formulate your business plan.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-formulate-your-business-plan-288x288-20200820.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Formulate your business plan."></div></div><p>Once you're familiar with the contents of a good business plan, you can get to writing one of your own.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>We've put together a free property management business plan template to help you do this. You'll find it toward the top of this page.</p></div><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>If necessary, you can adjust your management, marketing, or operational sections in response to new financial constraints.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-property-management-business-section3" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>3.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=form-a-legal-entity>Form a legal entity.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-property-management-business-section3-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=learn-about-the-main-business-structures>Learn about the main business structures.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-familiarize-yourself-with-the-key-business-structures-288x288-20200820.png?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Learn about the main business structures."></div></div><p>Your property management business needs to be set up as a legal entity. The structure that you choose is important for tax purposes.</p><p><strong>There are four basic business structures:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Sole proprietorship:</strong> A business that is owned and operated by just one person. All taxes and liability issues are the personal responsibility of the sole proprietor, who will likely need to use a schedule C form to report profits and losses.</li><li><strong>Partnership:</strong> Two or more partners who share the business's tax burden through individual tax returns.</li><li><strong>Limited liability corporation (LLC):</strong> An entity that assumes liability but still passes taxes on to the owners. May use corporate tax rules in some situations.</li><li><strong>Corporation:</strong> A distinct legal entity that assumes all liability and is taxed as a business at corporate tax rates. Has members and shareholders.</li></ul></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-property-management-business-section3-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>3.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=choose-your-preferred-business-structure>Choose your preferred business structure.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-review-mississippi-formation-options-288x288-20200907.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Choose your preferred business structure."></div></div><p>You can run your property management company using any one of the aforementioned structures. However, there are <strong>distinct advantages to setting up a corporation</strong>. For one thing, you can avoid the hefty tax burden that you may encounter if you choose to operate as a partnership. Additionally, you may want to avoid any structure that leaves you with personal liability.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>Consult a lawyer and a tax professional to determine which legal structure makes the most sense for your business.</p></div></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-property-management-business-section4" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>4.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=secure-financing>Secure financing.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-property-management-business-section4-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=calculate-your-expenses>Calculate your expenses.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-calculate-your-expenses-288x288-20200819.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Calculate your expenses."></div></div><p>Starting a property management company is not cheap. Your property management company will need money for things like:</p><ul><li>Office rent.</li><li>Payroll.</li><li>Supplies.</li><li>Building utilities.</li><li>Maintenance equipment.</li><li>Background check services.</li></ul><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>We've rounded up <a
href="#cost-of-starting-a-property-management-business">the most common expenses</a> associated with opening a property management business to help you get a sense of what you can expect to pay.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-property-management-business-section4-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=explore-a-variety-of-loan-options>Explore a variety of loan options.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-explore-a-variety-of-loan-options-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Explore a variety of loan options."></div></div><p>You'll want to explore multiple avenues when starting your property management company. You can meet with your local bank to find out more about small business loans, or you can find a qualified lender that offers SBA loans.</p><div
class="step-tip">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1" x="0px" y="0px" viewBox="0 0 512 512" style="enable-background:new 0 0 512 512;" xml:space="preserve">
<g>
<path
d="M256,0C114.844,0,0,114.844,0,256s114.844,256,256,256s256-114.844,256-256S397.156,0,256,0z M298.667,416    c0,5.896-4.771,10.667-10.667,10.667h-64c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667V256h-10.667c-5.896,0-10.667-4.771-10.667-10.667    v-42.667c0-5.896,4.771-10.667,10.667-10.667H288c5.896,0,10.667,4.771,10.667,10.667V416z M256,170.667    c-23.531,0-42.667-19.135-42.667-42.667S232.469,85.333,256,85.333s42.667,19.135,42.667,42.667S279.531,170.667,256,170.667z" data-original="#000000" class="active-path" data-old_color="#000000" fill="#4949E7"/>
</g>
</svg>
</span><p>As long as the interest rates aren't too high, loans can be an effective way of adding capital to your business so that you can purchase whatever you need to get your property management operations up and running.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-property-management-business-section4-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>4.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=apply-for-a-business-credit-card>Apply for a business credit card.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-apply-for-a-business-credit-card-288x288-20200819_2023-09-26-174359_icns.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Apply for a business credit card."></div></div><p>Business credit cards are great for short-term cash flow. Interest rates for credit cards are high, but if you just need a short term injection of capital to pay bills, a business credit card or line of credit might be the best solution.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-property-management-business-section5" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>5.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=obtain-state-licenses>Obtain state licenses.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-property-management-business-section5-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>5.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=find-out-which-license-and-or-permit-you-need>Find out which license and/or permit you need.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-find-out-which-license-and-or-permit-you-need-288x288-20200819.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Find out which license and/or permit you need."></div></div><p>Your state probably has a license or permit that you will need to obtain for your property management business. For example, in the state of California, property management companies are required to obtain a real estate broker's license.</p><p>Find out what specific criteria you need to meet by visiting your state's small business website.</p><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
d="M12 0c-6.627 0-12 5.373-12 12s5.373 12 12 12 12-5.373 12-12-5.373-12-12-12zm7 14h-5v5h-4v-5h-5v-4h5v-5h4v5h5v4z" fill="#4949E7"/>
</svg>
</span><p>We've rounded up a list of common, <a
href="#property-management-licenses-by-state">state-specific licensing requirements</a> to jump start your research process.</p></div><div
class="step-direction">
<span
class="icon">
<svg
xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
<path
