</span><p>You can use a website builder to create your own website.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-property-management-business-section8-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>8.2&nbsp;</span><h4 id=set-up-social-media-accounts>Set up social media accounts.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-set-up-social-media-accounts-288x288-20200819.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Set up social media accounts."></div></div><p>You can enhance your online presence by creating social media accounts for your property management company. Facebook and Twitter pages, in particular, will make it easier for people to engage with you.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-property-management-business-section8-step3" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>8.3&nbsp;</span><h4 id=join-your-local-chamber-of-commerce>Join your local chamber of commerce.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-join-your-local-chamber-of-commerce-288x288-20200819.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Join your local chamber of commerce."></div></div><p>Membership in your local chamber will give you access to exclusive business events and business-to-business networking opportunities. You may also be able to access local business services at a discounted price as a chamber member.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-property-management-business-section9" class="how-to-section"><div
class="section-title">
<span>9.&nbsp;</span><h3 id=hire-employees>Hire employees.</h3></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-property-management-business-section9-step1" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>9.1&nbsp;</span><h4 id=outline-your-staffing-requirements>Outline your staffing requirements.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-outline-your-staffing-requirements-288x288-20200818.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Outline your staffing requirements."></div></div><p>A growing property management business needs employees in order to keep up with services and continue to scale. <strong>Possible property management positions include:</strong></p><ul><li>Resident manager.</li><li>Maintenance coordinator.</li><li>Payroll administrator.</li><li>Office secretary.</li><li>Sales representative.</li><li>Property manager.</li></ul><p>Jot down which of these and other positions you'll need to fill, and how many people you'll need to do so.</p></div></div><div
id="how-to-start-a-property-management-business-section9-step2" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
